div1.p: Filed in the United States District Court
Order to Show Cause Why Writ of Habeas Corpus Should Not be Issued.
In the Matter of the Application of Moy Share Park for a Writ of Habeas Corpus

On reading and filing the petition of Moy Share Park duly signed and verified, whereby it appears that the said Moy Share Park is wrongfully and illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by Hon. Henry W.White, Commissioner of Immigration, at the United States Immigration Station at Seattle, Washington, and stating wherein the illegality exists, from which it appears that a Writ of Habeas Corpus ought to issue:
NOW, THEREFORE, it is by this Court

ORDERED, ADJUDGED AND DECREED that the said Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration at Seattle, Washington, be directed to show cause before Judge Neterer me in the court room of said court on the 19th day of April, A.D. 1920 at 10 AM. o'clock of said day, why said writ should not issue, to hold the person of and to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Moy Share Park, together with the time and cause of his detention.
Done in open court this 6th day of April, 1920.
